<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">

<head>
    <meta charset="UTF-8">
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
    <title>Service FAQ - BroqInsta Professional Support</title>
    <meta name="robots" content="index, follow">
    <meta name="description" content="Frequently asked questions about BroqInsta - learn about pricing, supported formats, download limits, and security.">
    <link rel="canonical" href="<%= siteUrl %>/faq">
    <meta property="og:type" content="website">
    <meta property="og:title" content="Service FAQ - BroqInsta Professional Support">
    <meta property="og:description" content="Frequently asked questions about BroqInsta - learn about pricing, supported formats, download limits, and security.">
    <meta property="og:image" content="<%= siteUrl %>/images/preview.png">
    <meta property="og:url" content="<%= siteUrl %>/faq">
    <meta property="og:site_name" content="BroqInsta">
    <meta name="twitter:card" content="summary_large_image">
    <meta name="twitter:title" content="Service FAQ - BroqInsta Professional Support">
    <meta name="twitter:description" content="Frequently asked questions about BroqInsta - learn about pricing, supported formats, download limits, and security.">
    <meta name="twitter:image" content="<%= siteUrl %>/images/preview.png">
    <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/style.css">
    <script src="/js/tailwind.js"></script>
</head>

<body class="bg-[#FAFBFC] min-h-screen flex flex-col">
    <%- include('partials/header') %>

    <main class="flex-grow container mx-auto px-4 py-12 max-w-3xl">
        <nav class="mb-8 text-sm font-medium text-gray-400" aria-label="Breadcrumb">
            <ol class="flex items-center space-x-2" itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/BreadcrumbList">
                <li itemprop="itemListElement" itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/ListItem">
                    <a href="/" itemprop="item" class="hover:text-purple-600 transition-colors"><span itemprop="name">Home</span></a>
                    <meta itemprop="position" content="1">
                </li>
                <li><span class="mx-2">/</span></li>
                <li itemprop="itemListElement" itemscope itemtype="https://schema.org/ListItem">
                    <span itemprop="name" class="text-gray-600">FAQ</span>
                    <meta itemprop="position" content="2">
                </li>
            </ol>
        </nav>

        <div class="text-center mb-24 stagger-in">
            <h1 class="text-64px font-black text-gray-900 mb-6">Expert Help.</h1>
            <p class="text-xl text-gray-500 font-medium leading-relaxed">Everything you need to know about the world's
                most reliable Instagram utility.</p>
        </div>

        <div class="space-y-6">
            <div class="glass-card p-8 rounded-3xl cursor-pointer group animate-on-scroll">
                <div class="flex justify-between items-center">
                    <h3 class="text-xl font-black text-gray-900">Is the service truly free?</h3>
                    <span class="text-2xl text-purple-600 group-hover:translate-x-2 transition-transform">→</span>
                </div>
                <p
                    class="mt-4 text-gray-500 font-medium leading-relaxed opacity-0 max-h-0 group-hover:opacity-100 group-hover:max-h-40 transition-all duration-500 overflow-hidden">
                    Yes. BroqInsta is and will always be free for public media extraction. We believe in open access to
                    digital content.
                </p>
            </div>

            <div class="glass-card p-8 rounded-3xl cursor-pointer group animate-on-scroll">
                <div class="flex justify-between items-center">
                    <h3 class="text-xl font-black text-gray-900">Do I need to authenticate?</h3>
                    <span class="text-2xl text-purple-600 group-hover:translate-x-2 transition-transform">→</span>
                </div>
                <p
                    class="mt-4 text-gray-500 font-medium leading-relaxed opacity-0 max-h-0 group-hover:opacity-100 group-hover:max-h-40 transition-all duration-500 overflow-hidden">
                    No. Our system is designed to fetch public content without ever requiring your Instagram
                    credentials. Your account remains 100% secure.
                </p>
            </div>

            <div class="glass-card p-8 rounded-3xl cursor-pointer group animate-on-scroll">
                <div class="flex justify-between items-center">
                    <h3 class="text-xl font-black text-gray-900">What is the maximum quality?</h3>
                    <span class="text-2xl text-purple-600 group-hover:translate-x-2 transition-transform">→</span>
                </div>
                <p
                    class="mt-4 text-gray-500 font-medium leading-relaxed opacity-0 max-h-0 group-hover:opacity-100 group-hover:max-h-40 transition-all duration-500 overflow-hidden">
                    We always fetch the original source file. If the content was uploaded in 1080p, that is exactly what
                    you will receive—bit-for-bit.
                </p>
            </div>

            <div class="glass-card p-8 rounded-3xl cursor-pointer group animate-on-scroll">
                <div class="flex justify-between items-center">
                    <h3 class="text-xl font-black text-gray-900">Supported media formats?</h3>
                    <span class="text-2xl text-purple-600 group-hover:translate-x-2 transition-transform">→</span>
                </div>
                <p
                    class="mt-4 text-gray-500 font-medium leading-relaxed opacity-0 max-h-0 group-hover:opacity-100 group-hover:max-h-40 transition-all duration-500 overflow-hidden">
                    We support high-bitrate MP4 for videos/reels and original JPEG for images.
                </p>
            </div>

            <div class="glass-card p-8 rounded-3xl cursor-pointer group animate-on-scroll">
                <div class="flex justify-between items-center">
                    <h3 class="text-xl font-black text-gray-900">Are there download limits?</h3>
                    <span class="text-2xl text-purple-600 group-hover:translate-x-2 transition-transform">→</span>
                </div>
                <p
                    class="mt-4 text-gray-500 font-medium leading-relaxed opacity-0 max-h-0 group-hover:opacity-100 group-hover:max-h-40 transition-all duration-500 overflow-hidden">
                    To ensure service stability for everyone, we implement a standard rate limit of 60 downloads per
                    hour per session.
                </p>
            </div>
        </div>

        <div class="mt-32 text-center py-12 border-t border-gray-100 animate-on-scroll">
            <p class="text-gray-400 font-bold mb-8 italic">Still have technical questions?</p>
            <a href="/contact" class="btn-primary px-12 py-5 font-black text-lg">Contact Technical Support</a>
        </div>
    </main>

    <%- include('partials/footer') %>
</body>

</html>